=== SESSION PATCH NOTES [SESSION 12 — THE WAITING HEART] ===
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GM INTENT (for future GMs):
This session had no combat, no heists, no clocks ticking down. It had a van ride, a conversation, a child's drawing, and a woman learning she could be held.

Anchor moved from survival to stewardship to something quieter: presence. He didn't fix Hana. He didn't promise to cure her. He just showed up, asked if she was okay, and offered a door. The million nuyen transfer—no strings, "so you know you can go anytime"—was power as freedom, not control.

The box hummed for Ren. Because of course it did. Children see what adults learn to ignore.

Thematic core: Presence. Stewardship. The moment waiting becomes being held.

────────────────────────────────

